1.9.20  4:17 pm   How does one approach lyrics? My musicality is improving and i pretty much know which track to take to improve but lyrics! A nightmare! there's no real system in place for them like there is for music (afaik) I have tried but is it like an every moment of every day kind of thing? I don't understand rhyme and rhythm i guess, any tips? thansk

     forget thinking about rhyme and rhythm. it will be there automatically. i think what you should do is open up a blank text file and start blowing your brains out. do this daily, forever. it will help. then the other thing to also do is start making songs with words and have competitions with yourself to see how bad you can make it. this will lead to good things i promise. the reason for this is that all music is bad, that's the reason we all like it so much
